<br>
Think this will hold true for everyone though. Even folks who can kite are gonna have  problems with mobs that can summon. And even with the old method this would have become an issue at 65 anyways, mobs would be light blue at 50, meaning blues would have been 51.<br>
<br>
I think the system is too restrictive, we're going to be herded into relatively few zones which will become quite overcrowded as time goes on and more people make it into the 60's. It's happened before, and can see happening again. maybe the new planes will support everyone, I sure hope so, but I have my doubts. Especially if some zones provide better rewards than others, then you will have everyone trying to cram into the &quot;good&quot; zone and the &quot;bad&quot; one being left basiclly unused.<br>
<br>
And not being able to solo as a magician sucks. Groups don't exactly beat down our door to have us join their groups. Not like an enchanter or cleric at any rate. I seldom get group invites, and generally only from guildies or friends. Trying to get into pickup groups takes a long time and usually requires some luck, it happens, but is very frustrating to spend hours doing little to nothing. On the other hand, I can login my cleric and get group invites from people I don't know in zones far away.<br>
<br>
