<br>
Now assuming you are 60+, if you're not epicced or have the 61 pet, try aggro-kiting.  PoP mobs have low hps, which means a couple of nukes and they're gone.  Don't depend on your pet tanking 300+ hitting mobs.  Depend on your nukes/rains/bolts to get them down asap.  Even with your epic and/or 61 pet, this should still be the philosophy of choice.  <br>
<br>
Once you get your new pet heal, this should all change.  I find it hard to believe that when a necro chaining his one (instead of 2-3) pet heal can kill a PoI mob with just his pet and a few DoTs and that mages, with your far superior pets, pet heals, DS's, and offensive expertise can somehow fail.  Either one party is missing something, or one party isn't telling.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, no wizard/druid/necro is going to be using their quad-kiting/root-rotting techniques on summoning mobs (and there are only a limited number of spots you can solo if you can't do summoning mobs), and here is where mages can shine.  Find an area where the aforementioned classes can't solo, and use a combination of chaining heals and rains to take down summoning mobs.  Sure, it's not nearly as easy as Luclin soloing, but what do you expect? This is the planes.<br>
<br>
I guess I should also mention that those quad-kiting wizards/druids in PoV should becareful - on test, there are rumors that those spots have pretty much been nerfed.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2466<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 8:38:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=390.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: So how does everyone else feel about not being able to s</span><hr size=1> I'm going to have to agree with Myrddin and Sasarella, my first instinct was that it sucked that soloing was so difficult..  But getting groups in PoP hasn't been difficult at all, and I've even gotten tells from random strangers asking me to join PoJ groups.<br>
