</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc@themagicianstower>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1191<br> <font color=#333333>(11/3/02 2:11:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=390.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: So how does everyone else feel about not being able to s</span><hr size=1> I enjoy grouping and it seems Verant did a very good job with making sure that everyone fits in well. The new spell load is nice (althought I am not impressed with the pets), and for the first time they gave spells to all classes that help them deal with things in a group setting. The mobs in PoP are very strange. They hit for a large amount of damage but not nearly as often as old world mobs. It seems this was done to prevent the boring, brainless complete heal cycle. I notice clerics having alot more fun now, and have to use various types of large/fast heals that are less efficient then CH. Mobs can do huge amounts of damage per round even slowed making slow+CH not the end all be all anymore.  My pet can tank some mobs for a little while then all of a sudden drops super fast.<br>
<br>
Only problem that I currently see for mages is lack of defense. We are very good offensively now but I believe that the new mobs are so strong that some form of defense is needed post 60. Our pets are even less protection then they once were.  I mean if not a spell some form of item that allows our pets to proc slow even if only 40%. That would help mages retain some form of solo ability. I made a mage because they could group or solo. I would like to maintain some form of solo ability. However if it doesn't happen I wouldn't be too upset about it. PoP is alot of fun, and grouping experience once again is far better then soloing.  Grouping in PoP is better then soloing at 60 by far.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
